    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-09-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-09-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="496"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.84A/9–2752: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 496<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d496fn1">Repeated to Jerusalem, London, Paris, Ankara, and
                        Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-09-27T19:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 27, 1952—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>498. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 422.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d496fn2">Not printed, but see <ref target="#d477fn3">footnote 3,
                            Document 477</ref>.</note> VD chief Amer Div Fon Ministry advises
                    informal mtg with Egypt <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> rep <persName
                        corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName> took place Thursday September 25 with
                    Col <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Ramati</persName> representing <gloss
                        target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> pursuant to arrangement described in ref tel.
                        <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> rep made specific suggestion that special
                    mtg be arranged on higher level to discuss (1) broadening scope of present
                    anti-infiltration agreement and (2) resolving questions of mutual interest
                    relating to shipping. Egypt’s rep said he wld consult superiors and report
                    result. <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> hopes discussion of point (1) may lead
                    to gen non-aggression agreement; and as to point (2) it proposes cover all
                    shipping matters including territorial waters, fishing rights and possibly
                    passage of shipping through Suez Canal (see <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss>s 467 and 497).<note n="3" xml:id="d496fn3">Neither
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
